Package Classes

Class EventLists

java.lang.Object
Classes.EventLists
public class EventLists extends Object
EventLists The EventLists class is responsible for managing lists related to event participants, including waiting lists, chosen lists, cancelled lists, and winners lists. This class also tracks maximum limits for entrants and winners, as well as optional geolocation information for participants.

    • EventLists

      public EventLists(String eventID, Integer maxWinners, Integer maxEntrants, boolean enableGeolocation, List<String> waitingList, List<String> chosenList, List<String> cancelledList, List<String> winnersList, Map<String,Object> locationList)
      Constructs an EventLists object with specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      eventID - Unique ID of the event
      maxWinners - Maximum number of winners allowed
      maxEntrants - Maximum number of entrants allowed
      enableGeolocation - Boolean flag to enable or disable geolocation for participants
      waitingList - List of users currently in the waiting list
      chosenList - List of users chosen for the event
      cancelledList - List of users who have cancelled their participation
      winnersList - List of users who are winners of the event
      locationList - Map containing location data for each user
